  "prompt": "What are the best dialogues from the movie Masaan?",
  "response": "**Masaan** (2015), directed by Neeraj Ghaywan, is a critically acclaimed Indian film known for its poignant storytelling and deeply moving dialogues. Here are some of the most memorable and impactful dialogues from the movie:\n\n1. **\"Jab tak jeete hain, tab tak karte hain, aur jab mar jaate hain, toh phir kya karte hain?\"**  \n   - This dialogue reflects the existential theme of the film, highlighting the struggle to find meaning in life despite its challenges.\n\n2. **\"Zindagi mein sab kuch mil jaaye, lekin pyaar na mile, toh kya maze?\"**  \n   - A heartfelt line that emphasizes the importance of love and human connection in life.\n\n3. **\"Yeh duniya bada zalim hai, bade bure kaam karti hai, lekin isme ek aisi cheez hai jo sabse badi hai... dosti aur pyaar.\"**  \n   - This dialogue speaks to the harsh realities of the world but also underscores the power of friendship and love.\n\n4. **\"Kyun darte ho maut se? Maut toh ek sundar sapna hai. Ek aisi neend hai jiska koi khatma nahi.\"**  \n   - A philosophical take on death, portraying it as a peaceful and eternal rest.\n\n5. **\"Zindagi mein sab kuch mil jaaye, lekin apne aap ko kho diya ho, toh kuch bhi nahi mila.\"**  \n   - A profound statement about self-identity and the importance of staying true to oneself.\n\n6. **\"Maut ke baad kya hota hai, koi nahi janta. Lekin zindagi ke baad kya hota hai, yeh hum sab jaante hain.\"**  \n   - A thought-provoking line that shifts focus from the uncertainty of death to the certainty of life\u2019s impact.\n\n7. **\"Humara dharm kya hai? Haram ko rokna, ya kaam karne walon ko paisa dena?\"**  \n   - This dialogue critiques societal norms and questions the morality of those in power.\n\n8. **\"Agar zindagi mein kisi cheez se darne ka hai, toh woh hai... khud se.\"**  \n   - A powerful reminder to confront one\u2019s own fears and insecurities.\n\nThese dialogues are deeply rooted in the film\u2019s exploration of life, death, love, and societal issues, making **Masaan** a cinematic experience that resonates long after the credits roll.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
